# =============================================================================
#  DVSA Earlier Slot Watcher — .gitignore
# =============================================================================
#
#  CRITICAL: any file matching *.personal.user.js MUST stay local. These files
#  may contain a driving licence number, booking reference, target test centre,
#  date window, instructor's blackout dates, and other personal information.
#  Never commit them. Anyone publishing this repo who runs the script locally
#  should keep their config in a *.personal.user.js file.
#
# =============================================================================

# Personal / private userscript copies (never commit)
*.personal.user.js
*.private.user.js
*.local.user.js

# PII-risk scratch files at the repo root. Stray files at the top level
# (page-source dumps for reference, RTF copies of DVSA pages, ad-hoc
# screenshots being processed before they go into docs/screenshots/, etc.)
# routinely contain a driving licence number, booking reference, full name,
# or current test date. The /-prefix anchors to the repo root, so intentional
# committed content under docs/, .github/, etc. is not affected. If you
# legitimately need a file with one of these extensions at the root, you can
# force-add it with `git add -f`, but that's an explicit override.
/*.rtf
/*.html
/*.htm
/*.txt
/*.png
/*.jpg
/*.jpeg
/*.gif
/*.bmp
/*.webp
/*.pdf
/*.docx
/*.doc
/*.xlsx
/*.xls
/*.csv

# Additional pattern-based safety net for filenames that clearly contain
# DVSA-page references regardless of where they live in the tree.
*page source*
*page-source*
*licence number*
*license number*
*booking ref*
*booking-ref*

# Internal planning notes (kept locally — public users don't need to see our backlog)
ROADMAP.md
PLANNING.md
NOTES.md
TODO.md
docs/superpowers/

# macOS metadata
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon?
._*

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.project
.settings/
.classpath

# AI / coding-assistant tooling (local settings, not for distribution)
.claude/
.cursor/
.aider*
.continue/

# Logs & temp
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig

# Node (only if you ever add tooling later)
node_modules/
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# Output / build artefacts
dist/
build/
*.min.js
